HEADWORD: Inocarpin
<hw>In`o*car"pin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'i`s</grk>, <grk>'ino`s</grk>, muscle + <grk>karpo`s</grk>
fruit.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A red, gummy, coloring matter,
